{
  "stem": "20609.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the way, I took the same train we took in 1940.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The difference was this time I took a sleeper, I was going first class.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] The other time, we went third class with the wooden benches, right.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I got to Copenhagen like in the morning and I went into a hotel and-- and then in the evening I went to the synagogue and the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I got there early and we shook hands.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "New rabbi.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had a different rabbi now, young-- young person.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after service, the rabbi and myself-- I forgot a lot of Danish so we talked in English-- and he said to me-- we were walking to the Jewish center and he says, I hope you forgive us.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I says, forgive you for what?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He says, we forgot to notify you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "See, the Jewish community was warned by the Danish underground because one German official notified that they're going to pick up the Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "All right?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They didn't-- they didn't notify us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I looked at him and I said, I wish you wouldn't have told me that because I just thought it was bad luck, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But that you forgot to notify, that puts another picture on us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If we were notified, if we were told-- see, they told-- the rabbi told-- on the podium he, says, hide, go-- go with some friends, but don't go to your apartments.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he volunteered to go back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He-- he was-- he stayed in his house because he said, I'm not going to leave and leave my people there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he went-- went with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they forgot to notify us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had to put that in.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
